What is the structure of your dataset?¶

there are 183,412 row in this dataset with 16 column (5 numeric, 8 string, 2 datetime and 1 boolean).

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I want to focus on the duration of each trip and it's relation with user type, gender, age , start and end stations.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I think that the duration_sec is the most important feature and it's strongly related to the other features.

Univariate Exploration¶

In [10]:
bins = np.arange(0,df['duration_sec'].max()+300,300)
plt.figure(figsize=[7,5])
plt.hist(data = df, x = 'duration_sec',bins = bins)

plt.title("Distribution of Trip duration")
plt.xlabel("duration in seconds")
plt.ylabel("number of trips")
plt.xlim([-100,6000])
plt.xticks(np.arange(300,6000+300,300),rotation = 90)
plt.show()

we should do a logarithmic scale because the histogram is skewed.

Discuss the distribution(s) of your variable(s) of interest. Were there any unusual points? Did you need to perform any transformations?¶

in the age distribution there was a beak in 26 years old then decreasing then increasing which was unusual, I performed a transformation in the duration distribution because the histogram was right skewed.

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions? Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form of the data? If so, why did you do this?¶

in the age distribution I substracted the birth year from 2019 to calculate the age , I sliced the start and end stations distrubtions because it's too large.

In [20]:
t = df
t['day'] = df['start_time'].dt.day
t = t.groupby('day')['duration_sec']

sb.lineplot(y = t.agg('mean'), x = t.agg('mean').index)
plt.title('mean trip duration for each day')
plt.xlabel('day')
plt.ylabel('duration in sec')
plt.show()

there is 3 peaks in days (10, 17, 23) with mean durations (943, 1048, 982), day 25 is the lowest trip duration mean (633).

Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. How did the feature(s) of interest vary with other features in the dataset?¶

trip duration is dependent on the age (people between 20 and 40 years old trip duration is higher than the older ages) and dependent on the user type.

Did you observe any interesting relationships between the other features (not the main feature(s) of interest)?¶

male trip duration is longer than female, and customer trip duration is longer than subscriber.
